summary: Just Kids (Peter Parker x Johnny Storm x O.C.) - Part Two
title: Just Kids (Peter Parker x Johnny Storm x O.C.) - Part Two
body:
Story Description:  Alexis Arsenault is trying her best to get used to being a sixteen year old superhero as her life continues to seemingly get worse and worse. She manages to get through with the help of her best friends and fellow superheroes Peter Parker (Spider Man) and Johnny Storm (Human Torch).

Part Description:  Alexis meets a new group of extraordinary extraterrestrials on her way back home, with the help of Tony Stark

Warnings:  Swearing probably

-Tony’s P.O.V-

I’m in the lab, messing around with some stuff to clear my head.

“Sir, Quinjet 27 is back online. It is in space, but there is a message for you. The message says ‘Good whatever time it is, Tony Stark, my name is Alexis Arsenault. I am lost in space and need help coordinating my way back home. This is vague but I hope you can help. Sorry for bugging you’,” FRIDAY tells me.

My eyes widen in surprise. This is the sixteen year old who went missing over a month ago. I use my phone and connect the camera that’s on the front of that ship to my phone. I sit down. She connects and I see the girl. She tears up when she sees my face.

“Oh my God that fucking worked,” she sighs in relief.

“Hey, Kid, I’m just gathering your coordinates now. I need you to head downwards, okay?” I tell her.

“Okay. Thank you so much,” she says, tears falling from her eyes.

“How did you get in space? How did the ship get into space?” I ask her curiously.

“This story is crazy,” she laughs, “This Valkyrie chick came to Earth after looking for someone to fight The Hulk, who somehow flew this ship into space. Anyway, I kinda won. I tricked him into fighting off the guards so I could run away and get into this ship and I hacked in using Black Widow’s voice. It’s been a long day.”

“You’ve been gone for a month, Kid,” I tell her.

“Jesus Christ, time flies when you’re having fun in space I guess,” she laughs.

I chuckle at her and shake my head.

“How many hits did the big guy get in?” he asks me.

“None,” I smile proudly.

Suddenly the camera glitches out and all I can hear is screaming before it shuts down. My eyes widen in surprise.

“Kid?” I ask, “Alexis, if you can hear me let me know.”

“The connection has failed, Sir,” FRIDAY says as my screen goes black.

I sigh heavily.

“Where does her brother live?” I ask FRIDAY.

-Peter Quill’s P.O.V-

“Rocket, you were supposed to be paying attention!” Gamora yells as we hit another ship.

“I was but then Groot stuck that dumb game in my face!” Rocket defends himself.

“I am Groot,” Groot replies sassily.

“It is a dumb game!” Rocket yells back.

I take control of the wheel.

“Peter, let’s make sure no one on that ship is hurt,” Gamora sighs.

“What’s in it for us?” Rocket asks.

“The joy of helping other people… And maybe some cash,” I reply.

Gamora gives me a look. I clear my throat.

“Everyone hold on,” I say, zooming down to the other ship.

There’s a girl hanging onto the edge of her ship. She looks terrified. Gamora opens up our side door. I go closer to the girl. Gamora holds her hand out. The other girl hops in and looks around in confusion.

“Are you alright?” Gamora asks her.

“Uh huh. Thank you,” she says, catching her breath.

“Where are ya headed? Your ship looks a little pretty broken,” I ask the girl.

“Uh, Earth. New York specifically,” she says.

“We never see people from Earth out here. This should be fun,” I smile.

“Are any of you from Earth?” she asks curiously as I start to fly her there.

“I am originally but I was abducted when I was eight,” I tell her.

“Ah,” she nods, looking around.

“Footloose?” she smiles.

“You know Footloose?” I ask her excitedly.

“Do I know Footloose?” she scoofs before taking out a square thing and plays the song Footloose.

“What is that?” I ask her curiously.

“A phone,” she tells me.

“There is no way that that is a phone,” I scoff.

She chuckles.

“You sound like an old man,” she tells me.

“He is an old man,” Rocket replies.

“Oh my God it’s a talking raccoon,” she smiles widely.

“Hey, I’m not just a talking raccoon, ya know. I’m also a genius, a thief, and an ultimate badass,” he replies.

She giggles and smiles at him.

“And adorable,” she replies, scratching behind his ear.

“Oh my… Why don’t any of you call me adorable and scratch my ear?” he asks us.

The girl laughs.

“I am Groot,” Groot chuckles.

“The tree talks too!?” she asks excitedly.

“I am Groot,” he replies.

“I have no idea what he’s saying but that is so cool,” she chuckles, “What are your names?”

“I’m Peter Quill, but you can call me Star Lord. The girl is Gamora, the big dummy sleeping back there through this whole thing is Drax, the raccoon is Rocket, and the tree is Groot. What’s your name?” I ask her.

“Alexis Arsenault,” she smiles, “Thank you for taking me back home.”

“Thank you for playing the Footloose soundtrack,” I tell her.

“They remade that movie not long ago,” she tells me.

“Seriously!?” I ask her with a smile.

“Yeah, it wasn’t as good,” she says.

“Did they remake the music?” I ask her.

“Footloose isn’t as good in this one,” she says before playing the shit remake.

“Turn off that garbage,” I tell her.

She laughs and nods.

“Will do,” she giggles.

“How old are you?” Gamora asks her curiously.

“I thought I was fifteen but time went by slower in Sakaar so I’m sixteen,” she answers.

“Wait, you made it out of Sakaar? Alone?” Rocket asks her curiously.

“Mhmm. I had a couple hints but yeah,” she nods.

“Can we keep her?” Rocket asks.

“As much as I would love to, I need to get back to my brother. I’m all the family he has, and he’s all I have,” she tells us.

“Well, if you’re ever bored we’ll always have room for one more,” Gamora tells her.

“Thank you,” she smiles.

“Hey, know what soundtrack is amazing?” Alexis asks me.

“What one?” I ask her curiously.

“Pretty Woman,” she smiles.

“I never saw that,” I reply.

“What!? Listen,” she says before playing the soundtrack and singing along.

She shows me music from her ‘phone’ the whole way to Earth. It’s fun. I land on the top of her apartment building.

“Here,” she says, handing me her phone and two cords.

“Wait, you’re giving this to me?” I ask her.

“Mhmm. It’s the least I could do. Thank you again, guys,” she says before getting out of the ship.

“Oh my… Why don’t any of you call me adorable and scratch my ear?” he asks us.

The girl laughs.

“I am Groot,” Groot chuckles.

“The tree talks too!?” she asks excitedly.

“I am Groot,” he replies.

“I have no idea what he’s saying but that is so cool,” she chuckles, “What are your names?”

“I’m Peter Quill, but you can call me Star Lord. The girl is Gamora, the big dummy sleeping back there through this whole thing is Drax, the raccoon is Rocket, and the tree is Groot. What’s your name?” I ask her.

“Alexis Arsenault,” she smiles, “Thank you for taking me back home.”

“Thank you for playing the Footloose soundtrack,” I tell her.

“They remade that movie not long ago,” she tells me.

“Seriously!?” I ask her with a smile.

“Yeah, it wasn’t as good,” she says.

“Did they remake the music?” I ask her.

“Footloose isn’t as good in this one,” she says before playing the shit remake.

“Turn off that garbage,” I tell her.

She laughs and nods.

“Will do,” she giggles.

“How old are you?” Gamora asks her curiously.

“I thought I was fifteen but time went by slower in Sakaar so I’m sixteen,” she answers.

“Wait, you made it out of Sakaar? Alone?” Rocket asks her curiously.

“Mhmm. I had a couple hints but yeah,” she nods.

“Can we keep her?” Rocket asks.

“As much as I would love to, I need to get back to my brother. I’m all the family he has, and he’s all I have,” she tells us.

“Well, if you’re ever bored we’ll always have room for one more,” Gamora tells her.

“Thank you,” she smiles.

“Hey, know what soundtrack is amazing?” Alexis asks me.

“What one?” I ask her curiously.

“Pretty Woman,” she smiles.

“I never saw that,” I reply.

“What!? Listen,” she says before playing the soundtrack and singing along.

She shows me music from her ‘phone’ the whole way to Earth. It’s fun. I land on the top of her apartment building.

“Here,” she says, handing me her phone and two cords.

“Wait, you’re giving this to me?” I ask her.

“Mhmm. It’s the least I could do. Thank you again, guys,” she says before getting out of the ship.

caption:
Artist Sign-Ups Open February 1st

Requirements to join:

  • To join, you must reblog one of the artist sign-up forms.
  • Artists must be able to create one (1) piece of art for each fic.
  • Like authors, you must keep your work private. However, you can start posting drafts one month before posting to tease the work, but nothing finished until publication day.
  • Art must be new, but can be in any medium you wish as long as it can be photographed and emailed.
  • Please contact us if you have any questions that aren’t addressed here at spidermanbigbang@gmail.com
